Summary:
A command line script that when given a hash tag, you get a list of urls from Twitter written to the STDOUT.

Usage:
ruby find_links.rb a_hash_tag

Example:
ruby find_links.rb kardashian

System Requirements:
Ruby 1.9.2p180
Ruby Gems 1.5.2
Mac OS X, 10.6.8
Not tested on other platforms

Installation:
bundle install

Tests:
Production test: ( Actually call out to http://search.twitter.com/ .)
cucumber features

Stubbed and unit tests:
rspec spec

Run all tests:
rake test

